<TITLE> Bangladesh Cooperative Bank may undergo conversion: adviser </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 24 (bdnews24.com)  The government is seriously thinking of converting Bangladesh Cooperative Bank into a specialised bank as part of restructuring, said local government adviser Anwarul Iqbal Sunday. "We are considering the issue," said the adviser at the 30th annual general meeting of the Bangladesh Cooperatives Bank. "A government committee has recently made recommendations for restructuring the bank," said Iqbal who also holds the labour and employment portfolio. Bangladesh Cooperative Bank usually extends loans to the agricultural sector through its various cooperatives. "The bank should also extend its activities to the disadvantaged," he said. There are currently five specialised bankBangladesh Krishi Bank and Rajshahi Krishi Unnayan, Bangladesh Shilpa Bank, Bangladesh Shilpa Rin Sangstha and BASIC Bankoperating in Bangladesh. bdn
